            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> We also have a DynamicBuffer, which this could maybe replace.\n\n`DynamicBuffer`, from the code I saw in `shell.c`, seems to be only the struct definition and has to be directly manipulated.\n\n> How does it compare to sds? Neither klib nor sds are paying attention to pull requests. sds appears to have actual documentation.\n\nWhen I suggested people noticed the tools we use to check the source code wouldn't play well with how `sds` deals with the `char *` pointers.\n\nAnd the advantage of `kstring` is that it's very small and we can tweak it to use our `x*` functions for memory handling just as we've been doing with the other `klib` structures.\n",
